    "detail": {
      "eyebrow": "Urban Operations Readiness",
      "expectTitle": "What to expect",
      "snapshotTitle": "Program snapshot",
      "snapshot": "Rising above the stark cold desert of Spiti, Mount Chau Chau Kang Nilda (6300m) is one of the most striking peaks dominating the skyline near Kaza. The mountain was first climbed in 1939 by a British expedition led by Major J.O.M. Roberts, and since then it has attracted mountaineers from across the world seeking a serious yet achievable Himalayan expedition peak. CCKN is known for its long glacier approaches, crevassed terrain, and steep snow slopes near the summit ridge, demanding endurance, sound mountain judgement, and the ability to move efficiently at high altitude. The climb is a true expedition experience, not a simple trekking objective. From 25 June to 06 July, Alpine Ops will attempt this iconic Spitian summit in a tightly managed expedition starting and ending in Kaza.",
